This experience is purely based on the service, poor management and lack of accountability from staff and manager during lunch today(10-21-19).  When it is about lunch downtown is full of choices both fine dine to take away salad and sandwich place. We mostly switch between placement to explore the place with best food and service.  Lenwich at 10 hanover is about 3 block from my office. Today I have visited and order my sandwich at 1.00 pm . And as expect I waited 30  ( exceptionally high wait time )mins but there was not call for me.  I went back and enquire about the status . The staff managing token follow up but come with no clear answer. I was running out of time and the restaurant was getting  empty. I follow back again and no resolution .  Finally, I have to cancel my order after wasting 38 mins waiting in queue. There was no effort from manager to take owenss and resolve the issue. how long it take to ready a misplaced sandwich order its no rocket science. Such experience make you red flag a place from your choice list. Highly not recommend such unprofessional place as a choice for people who go out to pick lunch in their limited work hour.

Solid sandwiches.  Their ordering process is very efficient (you order, get a beeper, pay, pickup sandwich when ready, go).  The price is about what you'd expect for a lunch in the city ($8-9ish).  The Lemwich (essentially a Reuben) is my go-to sandwich.  Plus I just found out that the ciabatta has less calories than my usual kaiser roll!  Witholding a star because a few of the grilled chicken sandwiches I tried were meh (especially the teriyaki one).  The place is kept pretty clean, bright, and modern looking.  A safe bet for a lunch spot.
